{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, we focus on wheeled and 12-degree-of-freedom (DOF) quadrupedal robots as they are the most widely used robot mobility types for navigation.",
    "In particular, wheeled robots have energy-efficient motion on flat terrains, whereas quadrupeds can traverse across diverse and challenging terrains [23].",
    "Our navigation policy is end-to-end in that it directly maps visual and proprioceptive observations to executable control commands without relying on embodiment-specific models.",
    "In this paper, we define executable action commands as the lowlevel action representations used in navigation and locomotion R Fig. 1.",
    "An overview of X-Nav."
  ]
}